# Cursor Rules for ThinkMODA Labs
# Auto-commit and deployment workflow

## Auto-Commit Instructions
After making any changes to the codebase, automatically run:
```bash
./scripts/auto-commit.sh
```

This will:
1. Check for changes
2. Commit with timestamp
3. Push to GitHub
4. Trigger automatic deployment

## Development Workflow
1. Make changes in Cursor
2. Test locally with `./start-dev.sh`
3. Run auto-commit script
4. Wait for GitHub Actions to deploy
5. Check live site at https://think-moda-labs.vercel.app

## File Structure
- `app/` - Next.js application pages
- `lib/services/` - Supabase service layer
- `scripts/` - Utility scripts
- `.github/workflows/` - GitHub Actions

## Environment Variables
All Supabase environment variables are configured in Vercel dashboard and GitHub secrets.

## Mobile Development
When editing from mobile:
1. Make changes in Cursor
2. Run auto-commit script
3. Monitor deployment in GitHub Actions
4. Check live site for updates 